Contributing Guidelines
1. Be Respectful: Communicate respectfully and constructively. Be open to feedback and differing viewpoints.
2. Follow the Process: Adhere to our contribution workflow. Submit issues or pull requests according to the guidelines provided.
3. Write Clear Commit Messages: Describe changes clearly and concisely in your commit messages.
4. Test Your Changes: Ensure your code is tested and does not break existing functionality. Provide test cases where applicable.
5. Document Your Work: Update documentation to reflect your changes. Include comments and explanations where necessary.
6. Code of Conduct: Abide by our Code of Conduct. Maintain a positive and collaborative environment.
7. Licensing: Ensure your contributions are compliant with our licensing terms and include the necessary acknowledgments.

Thank You For Contributing!
